=Episode 12=

21
00:02:40,660 --> 00:02:41,500
Did you hear me?

22
00:02:41,500 --> 00:02:42,410
This is important.

23
00:02:42,410 --> 00:02:43,750
I'll say it again.

24
00:02:43,750 --> 00:02:45,080
This mock exam will be held

25
00:02:45,080 --> 00:02:47,160
with other schools

26
00:02:47,160 --> 00:02:50,290
to give you a real exam experience.

27
00:02:50,290 --> 00:02:51,500
Based on the draw,

28
00:02:51,500 --> 00:02:53,620
you won't take the exam at our school.

29
00:02:53,620 --> 00:02:54,950
You will go to

30
00:02:54,950 --> 00:02:56,700
the assigned location for the exam.

31
00:02:59,750 --> 00:03:01,580
What? Relax.

32
00:03:01,580 --> 00:03:03,830
Our school will provide buses
for transportation that day,

33
00:03:03,830 --> 00:03:05,660
so make sure to gather on time.

34
00:03:05,660 --> 00:03:06,540
Did you hear that?

35
00:03:07,120 --> 00:03:09,290
Yes.

36
00:03:09,290 --> 00:03:11,620
And remember, don't be late.

37
00:03:13,950 --> 00:03:15,080
Didn't realize the problem

38
00:03:15,080 --> 00:03:16,580
was with all high schools,
not just ours.

39
00:03:19,700 --> 00:03:21,450
See? That's a parabola.

40
00:03:21,450 --> 00:03:22,500
Gao Tianyang,

41
00:03:22,500 --> 00:03:25,370
tell me the formula
for the trajectory of a parabola.

42
00:03:27,160 --> 00:03:28,870
The formula for the trajectory?

43
00:03:38,500 --> 00:03:41,000
Y squared equals...

44
00:03:47,330 --> 00:03:48,330
4...

45
00:03:49,250 --> 00:03:50,370
4c, something.

46
00:03:52,580 --> 00:03:54,250
cx.

47
00:03:54,250 --> 00:03:56,660
Y squared equals 4cx.

48
00:03:56,660 --> 00:03:58,740
Yes, Y squared equals 4cx.

49
00:03:58,750 --> 00:03:59,620
Thanks, Sheng Wang.

50
00:03:59,620 --> 00:04:00,950
Gao Tianyang, sit down please.

51
00:04:02,410 --> 00:04:03,410
Take out your test papers.

52
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:04,750
Let's review.

53
00:04:06,910 --> 00:04:07,960
Look at the first question.

54
00:04:09,000 --> 00:04:11,160
A 5-kilogram block
on a horizontal surface

55
00:04:11,160 --> 00:04:12,620
moves with an initial speed of 4 meters

56
00:04:12,620 --> 00:04:15,660
per second
against a 10-newton friction force.

57
00:04:50,470 --> 00:04:51,770
You have a good eye for things. Come on.

58
00:04:52,290 --> 00:04:53,370
I'll go shower, then.

59
00:04:57,330 --> 00:04:59,200
- This is awesome.
- This is the artsy version.

60
00:04:59,200 --> 00:05:00,040
This is awesome.

61
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:00,910
Whoa.

62
00:05:01,580 --> 00:05:03,040
I can't take it.

63
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,580
I'm out of shampoo.

64
00:05:21,580 --> 00:05:22,620
Anyone can lend me some?

65
00:05:22,620 --> 00:05:23,540
I have some.

66
00:05:23,790 --> 00:05:24,790
Here you are.

67
00:05:27,160 --> 00:05:28,120
We've got some good stuff.

68
00:05:28,120 --> 00:05:29,160
Wanna check it out?

69
00:05:31,370 --> 00:05:32,210
No.

70
00:05:33,000 --> 00:05:33,950
Not interested?

71
00:05:34,330 --> 00:05:35,170
Sheng.

72
00:05:36,040 --> 00:05:37,790
Wanna see something

73
00:05:37,790 --> 00:05:39,540
for grown-ups?

74
00:05:40,450 --> 00:05:41,290
A dirty book?

75
00:05:43,750 --> 00:05:45,290
I'll stick to my math book.

76
00:05:45,290 --> 00:05:47,250
Alright then, you have no taste.

77
00:05:47,580 --> 00:05:49,200
Shi, let's continue.

78
00:06:35,330 --> 00:06:36,330
Gao Tianyang,

79
00:06:36,750 --> 00:06:37,620
here you go.

80
00:06:38,290 --> 00:06:39,830
- Not at all.
- Thanks.

81
00:07:07,330 --> 00:07:09,330
How did you spill it?

82
00:07:09,330 --> 00:07:11,750
Idiot. Look, it's everywhere.

83
00:07:12,040 --> 00:07:13,700
Clean it up.

84
00:07:14,790 --> 00:07:16,040
How did you spill so much?

85
00:07:16,040 --> 00:07:17,410
You want some of this?

86
00:07:17,830 --> 00:07:19,580
- You want some of this?
- Why did you put it here?

87
00:07:19,580 --> 00:07:21,370
I didn't put it here. It's always here.

88
00:07:21,370 --> 00:07:22,950
Now, it's everywhere. Everywhere.

89
00:07:23,290 --> 00:07:24,450
Hurry up and clean it.

90
00:07:24,790 --> 00:07:25,680
You'd better clean it.

91
00:07:25,680 --> 00:07:26,870
It's precious.

92
00:07:26,880 --> 00:07:27,750
What the heck?

93
00:07:27,760 --> 00:07:29,500
Hey, you got it on my pants!

94
00:07:32,250 --> 00:07:34,080
Alright, alright, just take it away.

95
00:07:34,250 --> 00:07:41,040
♪My hidden stubbornness and fragility♪

96
00:07:41,380 --> 00:07:48,120
♪Your breath turned my world
upside down♪

97
00:07:49,540 --> 00:07:52,720
♪Silently following behind you♪

98
00:07:53,330 --> 00:07:57,030
♪I want to be you♪

99
00:07:59,010 --> 00:08:04,710
♪What exactly is our relationship♪

100
00:08:05,670 --> 00:08:12,330
♪I want more and more of you♪

101
00:08:13,000 --> 00:08:19,540
♪Will it turn into foam♪

102
00:08:25,870 --> 00:08:26,790
Sheng, morning!

103
00:08:29,910 --> 00:08:30,870
Whoa.

104
00:08:31,120 --> 00:08:33,250
Your smoky eye makeup is too much.

105
00:08:34,660 --> 00:08:35,750
Is it that obvious?

106
00:08:36,250 --> 00:08:38,200
Anyone with eyes can see it.

107
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:39,200
What happened?

108
00:08:42,080 --> 00:08:43,040
I couldn't sleep last night.

109
00:08:45,250 --> 00:08:46,830
I don't mean to bother you,

110
00:08:46,830 --> 00:08:48,330
but even if you didn't sleep well,

111
00:08:48,330 --> 00:08:49,910
you should eat something
to make up for it.

112
00:08:49,910 --> 00:08:52,200
Two eggs for breakfast isn't enough.

113
00:09:03,080 --> 00:09:04,250
Are you done,

114
00:09:04,250 --> 00:09:05,330
Gareth?

115
00:09:06,120 --> 00:09:07,200
Gareth?

116
00:09:08,200 --> 00:09:09,120
Speak it faster.

117
00:09:09,500 --> 00:09:11,200
Gareth... Get lost.

118
00:09:12,540 --> 00:09:13,410
But, come on,

119
00:09:13,700 --> 00:09:15,080
why couldn't you sleep?

120
00:09:15,700 --> 00:09:17,830
Did something happen in our dorm?

121
00:09:18,250 --> 00:09:19,090
No.

122
00:09:21,040 --> 00:09:21,880
Wang.

123
00:09:29,250 --> 00:09:31,000
Is that what you want to ask me?

124
00:09:31,370 --> 00:09:33,000
No, that's not what I meant.

125
00:09:33,620 --> 00:09:36,080
I want to ask you this question.

126
00:09:36,660 --> 00:09:39,540
If there are fish in a pond
and you plan to sell some,

127
00:09:39,540 --> 00:09:41,250
when's the best time to catch them?

128
00:09:43,950 --> 00:09:45,040
When you want to eat them.

129
00:09:45,500 --> 00:09:46,790
How many should you catch?

130
00:09:49,950 --> 00:09:51,290
How many?

131
00:09:54,830 --> 00:09:56,160
As many as you want to eat.

132
00:09:57,620 --> 00:09:58,500
Definitely not.

133
00:09:58,500 --> 00:09:59,950
Wanna bet? I'll ask Sheng.

134
00:09:59,950 --> 00:10:01,700
Go ahead. Ask him.

135
00:10:02,870 --> 00:10:04,330
Sheng, let me ask you.

136
00:10:04,330 --> 00:10:05,700
In the last chemistry class,

137
00:10:05,700 --> 00:10:06,950
we learned about fluoride,

138
00:10:06,950 --> 00:10:08,950
the stuff in toothpaste.

139
00:10:09,290 --> 00:10:11,290
What was the key point of that section?

140
00:10:13,750 --> 00:10:14,870
What was the key point?

141
00:10:20,160 --> 00:10:21,160
To prevent cavities.

142
00:10:27,330 --> 00:10:28,700
What's so funny, you guys?

143
00:10:28,700 --> 00:10:30,160
To prevent cavities.

144
00:10:30,160 --> 00:10:31,540
What is it?

145
00:10:33,580 --> 00:10:34,580
Sheng,

146
00:10:34,580 --> 00:10:36,290
why do you have such bad dark circles?

147
00:10:36,500 --> 00:10:38,200
Oh, I didn't sleep well.

148
00:10:39,000 --> 00:10:40,580
There are eggs right here.

149
00:10:40,580 --> 00:10:43,290
The internet says
you can roll hard-boiled eggs

150
00:10:43,290 --> 00:10:44,910
over your dark circles
to help with them.

151
00:10:45,410 --> 00:10:46,660
- You can give it a try.
- Yeah.

152
00:10:47,330 --> 00:10:49,160
I know someone gave me
these eggs for a reason.

153
00:10:50,040 --> 00:10:50,880
Like this?

154
00:10:50,890 --> 00:10:52,750
- No.
- You should take them out.

155
00:10:56,120 --> 00:10:56,960
Like this?

156
00:10:57,250 --> 00:10:58,090
Roll them around.

157
00:11:00,040 --> 00:11:01,040
It's hot.

158
00:11:05,290 --> 00:11:06,410
Time for class.

159
00:11:06,410 --> 00:11:07,620
Did you finish your homework?

160
00:11:07,750 --> 00:11:08,620
Get back to your seats.

161
00:11:08,620 --> 00:11:10,000
I can eat them if you are not going to.

162
00:11:19,700 --> 00:11:20,830
Why couldn't you sleep?

163
00:11:23,290 --> 00:11:24,160
Because

164
00:11:24,160 --> 00:11:25,830
I had a nightmare last night.

165
00:12:07,120 --> 00:12:08,080
Linzi.

166
00:12:11,750 --> 00:12:13,200
Director Xu wants to see me.

167
00:12:13,620 --> 00:12:14,500
I'll be right back.

168
00:13:04,540 --> 00:13:05,620
You freaked me out.

169
00:13:05,620 --> 00:13:07,000
What? Are you watching a horror movie?

170
00:13:07,620 --> 00:13:09,080
Yeah. Where's Tian?

171
00:13:09,580 --> 00:13:10,830
He went running.

172
00:13:13,700 --> 00:13:14,750
Actually,

173
00:13:14,750 --> 00:13:16,620
I was just trying to build my courage.

174
00:13:16,620 --> 00:13:18,950
I used to think I wasn't scared

175
00:13:18,950 --> 00:13:20,290
and even laughed at Gao.

176
00:13:20,750 --> 00:13:21,830
But the other day,

177
00:13:22,540 --> 00:13:24,950
I walked someone back to the dorm.

178
00:13:25,200 --> 00:13:26,910
The hallway was pitch black.

179
00:13:27,200 --> 00:13:28,950
Suddenly, someone tapped me
on the shoulder.

180
00:13:29,870 --> 00:13:31,080
It scared me to death.

181
00:13:32,120 --> 00:13:33,790
So how's it going?

182
00:13:34,540 --> 00:13:36,620
Not great, or you wouldn't
have scared me.

183
00:13:38,830 --> 00:13:40,120
How about I watch it with you

184
00:13:40,120 --> 00:13:41,620
to make it up to you?

185
00:13:42,660 --> 00:13:44,080
Sure, let's do it.

186
00:13:49,410 --> 00:13:50,450
But

187
00:13:50,450 --> 00:13:51,580
aren't you scared?

188
00:13:53,160 --> 00:13:56,250
Weren't you sharing a bed
with Tian back then?

189
00:13:58,540 --> 00:13:59,410
Oh, forget it.

190
00:13:59,410 --> 00:14:01,080
Come on. Two negatives make a positive.

191
00:14:01,080 --> 00:14:02,540
- Yeah.
- Here you go.

192
00:14:02,540 --> 00:14:03,380
Okay.

193
00:14:19,620 --> 00:14:21,620
Oh, man. I was scared by you.

194
00:14:22,450 --> 00:14:23,410
That is terrifying.

195
00:14:32,950 --> 00:14:33,950
I got a text.

196
00:14:33,950 --> 00:14:34,790
Oh.

197
00:14:42,040 --> 00:14:43,250
Who sent it?

198
00:14:43,250 --> 00:14:44,620
Why are you grinning like that?

199
00:14:44,620 --> 00:14:45,750
Who else could it be?

200
00:14:46,290 --> 00:14:47,130
It's He Shi.

201
00:14:47,790 --> 00:14:49,580
She told me to build my courage.

202
00:14:50,370 --> 00:14:51,500
What a love-struck fool.

203
00:14:56,910 --> 00:14:58,250
Are you in a relationship?

204
00:14:58,250 --> 00:14:59,620
(I finally feel like I'm going to live
in the dorm. Tell me it's true.)

205
00:14:59,620 --> 00:15:01,290
I'm always right about spotting students

206
00:15:01,290 --> 00:15:02,500
(It's true.)
who are in a relationship.

207
00:15:02,500 --> 00:15:04,040
You must be in one.

208
00:15:04,750 --> 00:15:06,000
Sir, I'm not.

209
00:15:06,000 --> 00:15:07,580
I was really texting Jiang Tian.

210
00:15:07,580 --> 00:15:08,450
I don't believe it.

211
00:15:08,750 --> 00:15:09,750
Here.

212
00:15:09,750 --> 00:15:11,330
Unlock it and show me. Now.

213
00:15:17,790 --> 00:15:19,000
Oh, it is Jiang Tian.

214
00:15:21,700 --> 00:15:22,790
I've noticed that

215
00:15:23,500 --> 00:15:24,950
no matter how fierce a girl is,

216
00:15:24,950 --> 00:15:26,750
once she's in love,

217
00:15:27,620 --> 00:15:29,160
she becomes really cute.

218
00:15:31,870 --> 00:15:32,750
Why?

219
00:15:34,870 --> 00:15:37,410
I never knew a girl with dimples

220
00:15:37,410 --> 00:15:38,750
could be so charming.

221
00:15:39,160 --> 00:15:40,250
Do you know

222
00:15:40,750 --> 00:15:42,200
how cute when she smiles?

223
00:15:42,200 --> 00:15:44,040
She has a little dimple right here.

224
00:15:44,700 --> 00:15:47,370
And you know what? When her hair

225
00:15:47,370 --> 00:15:48,660
catches the sunlight,

226
00:15:48,660 --> 00:15:50,370
it lightens up.

227
00:15:52,830 --> 00:15:54,620
She has fair skin

228
00:15:54,620 --> 00:15:55,830
and long legs.

229
00:15:59,160 --> 00:16:00,410
She is adorable.

230
00:16:00,790 --> 00:16:02,580
Her smile makes me feel warm.

231
00:16:12,370 --> 00:16:15,410
How can you be sure

232
00:16:15,830 --> 00:16:17,410
that she's the one you like?

233
00:16:19,790 --> 00:16:24,410
There are many girls with dimples,
long legs, and fair skin.

234
00:16:24,410 --> 00:16:27,410
How can you be sure she's the one?

235
00:16:28,160 --> 00:16:30,330
This isn't even a question.

236
00:16:30,330 --> 00:16:31,410
Whether you like someone or not,

237
00:16:31,410 --> 00:16:32,910
you just know it yourself.

238
00:16:33,660 --> 00:16:35,620
When you like someone,

239
00:16:35,620 --> 00:16:37,790
you can't see anyone else.

240
00:16:40,950 --> 00:16:43,040
Like when I won first place
in the sprint

241
00:16:44,160 --> 00:16:45,910
at the School Anniversary,

242
00:16:46,450 --> 00:16:48,620
all my classmates
came to celebrate with me,

243
00:16:50,410 --> 00:16:52,330
but I could only saw He Shi.

244
00:16:53,450 --> 00:16:55,000
She gave me a bottle of water.

245
00:16:57,120 --> 00:16:58,040
And then,

246
00:16:58,040 --> 00:16:59,870
I accidentally brushed against her.

247
00:17:01,040 --> 00:17:02,040
She...

248
00:17:03,750 --> 00:17:05,120
I got so nervous.

249
00:17:06,830 --> 00:17:08,410
I even...

250
00:17:10,120 --> 00:17:13,120
I even... I even wanted to kiss her.

251
00:17:33,200 --> 00:17:34,790
I'll go get some water.

252
00:17:42,540 --> 00:17:43,660
Hey, Shi Yu.

253
00:17:44,160 --> 00:17:45,580
Oh, Tian, you're back.

254
00:17:46,200 --> 00:17:47,200
What's wrong with him?

255
00:17:48,160 --> 00:17:49,040
What do you mean?

256
00:17:50,080 --> 00:17:51,160
What were you guys doing?

257
00:17:52,750 --> 00:17:54,540
We were watching a horror movie.

258
00:17:54,540 --> 00:17:55,870
I wanted to build some courage.

259
00:17:55,870 --> 00:17:57,200
Sheng Wang just got back,

260
00:17:57,200 --> 00:17:59,040
so I asked him to join me.

261
00:17:59,870 --> 00:18:00,790
Him?

262
00:18:01,080 --> 00:18:01,920
Yeah.

263
00:18:02,450 --> 00:18:03,870
So, you both were trembling together?

264
00:18:04,370 --> 00:18:05,410
No, no.

265
00:18:05,410 --> 00:18:07,160
Sheng's got nerves of steel.

266
00:18:07,160 --> 00:18:08,450
I was terrified,

267
00:18:08,450 --> 00:18:09,910
but he stayed completely calm.

268
00:18:11,910 --> 00:18:13,410
He's got nerves of steel?

269
00:18:13,750 --> 00:18:14,590
Yeah.

270
00:18:16,950 --> 00:18:17,950
Are you scared?

271
00:18:20,040 --> 00:18:21,830
How about we share my bed?

272
00:18:25,580 --> 00:18:26,450
Hey.

273
00:18:27,250 --> 00:18:28,790
Why are you standing at the door?

274
00:18:30,370 --> 00:18:31,580
Aren't you scare...

275
00:18:31,950 --> 00:18:32,910
What's wrong?

276
00:18:35,450 --> 00:18:36,500
Nothing.

277
00:18:38,480 --> 00:18:44,040
♪Unable to embrace you, I fell♪

278
00:18:47,370 --> 00:18:49,540
This isn't even a question.

279
00:18:49,540 --> 00:18:50,620
Whether you like someone or not,

280
00:18:50,620 --> 00:18:52,120
you just know it yourself.

281
00:18:52,120 --> 00:18:57,550
♪Like Night and Day residing in the Sky♪

282
00:18:58,760 --> 00:19:02,410
♪Where is the end of the story♪

283
00:19:02,750 --> 00:19:05,470
♪Who decides if it is love♪

284
00:19:05,470 --> 00:19:11,140
